actor Manager as Organization billing manager
actor Member as Organization member
actor Operator as Organization admin/editor
participant Client as React admin/API client
participant Tenant as Auth and tenant middleware
participant Billing as Billing routes
participant Quota as Quota service
participant StripeSvc as Stripe billing service
participant Stripe as Stripe API/webhook sender
participant Ops as Beta/GA routes
participant Audit as Audit/email services
participant DB as PostgreSQL

rect rgb(238, 247, 255)
    Note over Member,DB: Plan listing and current usage [IMPLEMENTED]
    Member->>Client: Open Billing page
    Client->>Tenant: GET /api/billing/plans with tenant headers
    Tenant->>Billing: TenantContext; billing path is API-quota exempt
    Billing->>DB: SELECT active plans ordered by price
    Billing->>Billing: Mark Stripe checkout availability from plan/configured price IDs
    Billing-->>Client: Free, Pro, and Enterprise plan metadata
    Client->>Tenant: GET /api/billing/usage
    Tenant->>Billing: TenantContext
    Billing->>Quota: usage_summary
    Quota->>DB: Ensure/load subscription and effective plan
    Quota->>DB: Recalculate members, content records, and media bytes
    Quota->>DB: UPSERT three rebuildable usage_counters
    Quota->>DB: Read current API request counter
    Billing-->>Client: Subscription, limits, usage, and exceeded flags
end

rect rgb(238, 255, 242)
    Note over Manager,Stripe: Checkout creation [IMPLEMENTED, EXTERNAL/LOCAL STEPS ARE NON-ATOMIC]
    Manager->>Client: Choose paid plan
    Client->>Tenant: POST /api/billing/checkout
    Tenant->>Billing: TenantContext
    Billing->>Billing: require_org_billing_manager
    Billing->>StripeSvc: create_checkout_session
    StripeSvc->>DB: Load active plan and Stripe price ID
    StripeSvc->>Quota: Ensure default local subscription
    StripeSvc->>DB: Load provider_customer_id
    alt Customer ID missing
        StripeSvc->>DB: Load organization name and owner email
        StripeSvc->>Stripe: POST /v1/customers
        Stripe-->>StripeSvc: Stripe customer ID
        StripeSvc->>DB: UPDATE local subscription provider/customer ID
        Note over StripeSvc,DB: Stripe customer creation and local update are not transactional [PARTIAL]
    end
    StripeSvc->>Stripe: POST /v1/checkout/sessions with organization/plan metadata
    alt Stripe request fails
        Stripe-->>Billing: ServiceUnavailable; no checkout audit
    else Session created
        Stripe-->>StripeSvc: Session ID and URL
        Billing->>Audit: Record billing.checkout.create after external call
        Audit->>DB: INSERT audit_logs
        alt Audit fails
            Note over Billing,Stripe: Stripe session already exists and is not canceled [PARTIAL]
            Billing-->>Client: Mapped audit error
        else Audit succeeds
            Billing-->>Client: Checkout session URL
        end
    end
end

rect rgb(250, 248, 255)
    Note over Manager,Stripe: Customer portal [IMPLEMENTED]
    Manager->>Client: Open customer portal
    Client->>Tenant: POST /api/billing/portal
    Tenant->>Billing: TenantContext
    Billing->>Billing: require_org_billing_manager
    Billing->>StripeSvc: create_customer_portal_session
    StripeSvc->>DB: Load existing provider_customer_id
    alt Customer ID absent
        Billing-->>Client: Validation error
    else Customer ID present
        StripeSvc->>Stripe: POST /v1/billing_portal/sessions
        Stripe-->>StripeSvc: Portal URL
        Billing->>Audit: Record billing.portal.create after external call
        Audit->>DB: INSERT audit_logs
        Billing-->>Client: Portal URL
    end
end

rect rgb(255, 238, 245)
    Note over Stripe,DB: Stripe webhook signature, idempotency, ordering, and subscription update [IMPLEMENTED]
    Stripe->>Billing: POST /api/billing/stripe/webhook with raw body and Stripe-Signature
    Billing->>StripeSvc: handle_webhook
    StripeSvc->>StripeSvc: Verify timestamp tolerance and HMAC-SHA256 v1 signature
    alt Signature/config/payload invalid
        StripeSvc-->>Stripe: 401, 400, or 503 mapped error; no event row
    else Signature and payload valid
        critical Billing event transaction with RLS bypass [IMPLEMENTED]
            StripeSvc->>DB: BEGIN; set zinhar.rls_bypass=true
            StripeSvc->>DB: INSERT billing_events status=processing ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING
            alt Duplicate provider_event_id
                StripeSvc->>DB: COMMIT without reprocessing
                StripeSvc-->>Stripe: already_processed
            else New supported event
                StripeSvc->>DB: Resolve organization and plan
                StripeSvc->>DB: UPSERT organization_subscriptions only when event timestamp is not older
                Note over StripeSvc,DB: Events without a provider created timestamp pass the ordering guard [PARTIAL] AMB-054
                alt Subscription row applied
                    StripeSvc->>DB: UPDATE billing_events status=processed
                    StripeSvc->>DB: INSERT billing.stripe_webhook.process audit log
                else Stale provider event
                    StripeSvc->>DB: UPDATE billing_events status=ignored
                    StripeSvc->>DB: INSERT billing.stripe_webhook.ignore audit log
                end
                StripeSvc->>DB: COMMIT subscription/event/audit atomically
                StripeSvc-->>Stripe: processed or ignored
            else Unsupported event type
                StripeSvc->>DB: UPDATE billing_events status=ignored
                StripeSvc->>DB: COMMIT
                StripeSvc-->>Stripe: ignored
            end
        option Processing error after event insertion
            StripeSvc->>DB: Attempt UPDATE billing_events status=failed with error
            alt Transaction remains usable
                StripeSvc->>DB: COMMIT failed event record
            else PostgreSQL transaction is already aborted
                DB-->>StripeSvc: Failed-status update/commit also fails; transaction rolls back on drop
            end
            StripeSvc-->>Stripe: Mapped non-success response
        end
    end
    Note over Quota,DB: Subsequent quota checks load the updated plan/status; canceled/incomplete subscriptions fall back to Free [IMPLEMENTED]
end

rect rgb(255, 252, 238)
    Note over Manager,DB: Usage rebuilding and audit [IMPLEMENTED, NON-ATOMIC COUNTERS]
    Manager->>Client: Click Rebuild usage
    Client->>Tenant: POST /api/billing/usage/rebuild
    Tenant->>Billing: TenantContext
    Billing->>Billing: require_org_billing_manager
    Quota->>DB: Calculate members, content records, and media bytes
    Quota->>DB: UPSERT members counter via tenant connection
    Quota->>DB: UPSERT content_records counter via another tenant connection
    Quota->>DB: UPSERT media_bytes counter via another tenant connection
    alt Any counter write fails
        Note over Quota,DB: Earlier counters may already be committed; no encompassing transaction [PARTIAL]
        Billing-->>Client: Mapped error
    else Rebuild succeeds
        Billing->>Audit: Record billing.usage.rebuild
        Audit->>DB: INSERT audit_logs in a separate transaction
        Billing->>Quota: Build response; usage_summary rebuilds counters again
        Billing-->>Client: Refreshed usage JSON
    end
end

rect rgb(255, 244, 238)
    Note over Member,DB: Beta feedback submission [IMPLEMENTED]
    Member->>Client: Submit beta feedback
    Client->>Tenant: POST /api/beta/feedback
    Tenant->>Ops: TenantContext
    Ops->>Ops: Validate category, severity, title, description, URL, and metadata
    critical Feedback and audit transaction [IMPLEMENTED]
        Ops->>DB: BEGIN with tenant RLS context
        Ops->>DB: INSERT beta_feedback
        Ops->>DB: INSERT beta.feedback.create audit log
        Ops->>DB: COMMIT
    option Validation or write fails
        Ops-->>Client: Mapped error; transaction rolls back
    end
    Ops-->>Client: Created feedback
end

rect rgb(238, 250, 255)
    Note over Operator,DB: GA blocker update [IMPLEMENTED]
    Operator->>Client: Update blocker priority/status/owner/due date
    Client->>Tenant: PATCH /api/beta/ga-blockers/{blocker_id}
    Tenant->>Ops: TenantContext
    Ops->>Ops: Require organization admin or editor; validate status and priority
    critical Blocker and audit transaction [IMPLEMENTED]
        Ops->>DB: BEGIN with tenant RLS context
        Ops->>DB: UPDATE beta_ga_blockers for organization
        Ops->>DB: INSERT beta.ga_blocker.update audit log
        Ops->>DB: COMMIT
    option Authorization, validation, or write failure
        Ops-->>Client: Mapped error; transaction rolls back
    end
    Ops-->>Client: Updated GA blocker
end
